<p>There is a brief but interesting interview (more like interrogation) with Valve's Jess Cliffe, co-creator of Counter-Strike over at <a href="http://www.computerandvideogames.com/r/?page=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/news/news_story.php?id=101811">C&VG</a> (computer and video games). If you get the chance have a read. But in my opinion the person asking the question shows little respect for Jess Cliffe and Valve. As a reader/player I really wanted to know about what great features CS:Condition Zero would have, and not why the long delay.
